  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">William Lloyd Garrison is waiting for the arrival of Mr. and Mrs. May, with their dear children. Garrison is to speak at the quarterly meeting of the [New England] Anti-Slavery Society on the 29th. The anti-slavery convention for Middlesex County is to be held October 1st in Groton. Dr. Amos Farnsworth is anxious to secure May&apos;s services there. Durant&apos;s balloon ascension was beautiful. Ruffians from Canterbury, Conn., broke up Prudence Crandall&apos;s school.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">On the bottom of page four of this manuscript, there is a separate note by Mrs. Helen Eliza Garrison to Mrs. Samuel Joseph May (Lucretia Flagge Coffin May). The Garrisons are anticipating the pleasure of a visit from Mrs. May.</subfield>
  </datafield>
